✅ OWASP ZAP Scanner – Short Note
🔷 Introduction

OWASP ZAP (Zed Attack Proxy) is one of the most popular open-source web application security testing tools developed by the OWASP.
It is used to find security vulnerabilities in web applications during development and testing phases.

ZAP acts as a proxy between the user (browser) and the web application, allowing it to intercept, inspect, and modify HTTP/HTTPS requests and responses.

🔥 Key Features of OWASP ZAP
✔ 1. Intercepting Proxy
Captures and analyzes web traffic between browser and server
Helps in identifying vulnerabilities
✔ 2. Automated Scanner
Automatically scans web applications
Detects common vulnerabilities like SQL Injection, XSS, etc.
✔ 3. Passive and Active Scanning
Passive Scan: Observes traffic without modifying it
Active Scan: Sends attacks to identify vulnerabilities
✔ 4. Spidering (Crawling)
Explores all pages of a web application
Finds hidden URLs and inputs
✔ 5. Fuzzer
Sends random or unexpected data to inputs
Helps detect security weaknesses
✔ 6. Authentication Testing
Tests login systems and session handling
✔ 7. User-Friendly Interface
Easy to use GUI
Suitable for beginners and professionals
⚙️ Working of OWASP ZAP
Configure browser to use ZAP as proxy
Send requests through ZAP
ZAP captures and analyzes requests/responses
Perform scanning (passive/active)
Generate vulnerability report
📌 Example: Detecting SQL Injection
🔹 Scenario:

A login page accepts username and password.

🔹 Attack using ZAP:
Intercept login request
Modify input:
' OR 1=1 --
🔹 Result:
ZAP detects vulnerability
Login bypass occurs
🔹 Output:

ZAP report shows:

SQL Injection vulnerability
Risk level: High
Suggested fix: Use prepared statements
🎯 Advantages of OWASP ZAP
Free and open-source
Easy to use
Supports automated and manual testing
Regular updates
⚠️ Limitations
May produce false positives
Requires proper configuration for advanced testing
